  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And some people were prepared to show them the bunkers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they discovered the bunkers, either by informers, or by dogs, or by other means, or simply-- and they were getting people.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were throwing grenades, and gas grenades into the bunkers, and into the people that were going out, and getting them off still to Treblinka.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so they finished everything in the-- but even after they finished with-- everything was burned, and all the bunkers, most of the bunkers, were uncovered, they still were not-- didn't rest until the whole of the ghetto, which was burnt, the burnt houses, were then exploded.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They had then-- they had then engineers, who were systematically exploding all of the remnants, the walls of the houses, which were still there, so that at the end of the war in late '44, of ghetto, apart from the prison, and the church, and a couple of other things, all this huge area was just like-- roughly like Sahara Desert, mounds of rubble, rubble.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was nothing left except rubble.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And, of course, they discovered all of the bunkers that were there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I don't see think any bunker-- any bunker survived.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
